Description . Holotype male. Body length 2.3 mm; wing length 2.3 mm. Width of frons approximately subequal to anterior ocellus width. Antenna velvety black. Palpus brown. Thorax shiny black. Thoracic setae: 3–4 dorsocentrals, 2–3 antepronotals, 1–3 proepisternals, 1–2 pairs of scutellars. Legs shiny yellow with apex of hind femur, almost entire hind tibia and all tarsomeres 3–5 black. Hind femur with 1 anteroventral seta slightly stronger at distal third. Wing (
Fig. 62
, paratype ). Halter dark brown, partially white at knob. Abdomen shiny black. Terminalia with tergite 8 (
Fig. 45
) short, without sinus posteriorly and with shallow sinus anteriorly. Epandrium (
Fig. 46
) with anterodorsal and posterodorsal lobes short, almost same height. Anterior cercus wider ventrally (
Fig. 47
), with internal small process dorsally (
Fig. 49
); posterior cercus elongate longitudinally, curved inward. Cercal bridge (
Fig. 49
) small, projecting anteriorly from ventral margin of anterior cercus. Ventral projection of cercus widened, with setae placed on small protuberance (
Fig. 48
). Hypandrium (
Fig. 47
) with few uniseriated setae medially, without sinus on posterior margin.

Female. Fore coxa black; hind femur banded with yellow at base and subapically, black at middle and apically. Mid tibia with 1 slightly longer posterodorsal seta near middle. Hind tibia without pinnate setae. Wing (
Fig. 63
). Terminalia with tergite 8 and sternite 8 same length (
Fig. 50
). Tergite 8 (
Fig. 51
) with distal sinus. Sternite 8 (
Fig. 52
) with small distinct lateral sinus at basal third. Genital fork (
Fig. 53
) small, with elongate lateral arms. Genital chamber membranous.
